This directory will contain the server-side implementation of the GaS.

Installation Guide:

1. create gate-service empty dir in tomcat/webapps
2. Checkout gate-service from SVN
3. execute ant war.complete inside server folder
4. extract content gate-service/server/gate-service.war into tomcat/webapps/gate-service folder
5. edit the following lines in workerBeans.xml in tomcat/webapps/gate-service/WEB-INF/spring folder:

 <!-- Use dummy proxies for doc service and executive -->
 <bean id="executiveProxyFactory"
   class="gleam.executive.proxy.dummy.DummyExecutiveProxyFactory" />

 <bean id="docServiceProxyFactory"
   class="gleam.docservice.proxy.dummy.DummyDocServiceProxyFactory" />

to match real impl, e.g:

<bean id="executiveProxyFactory"
   class="gleam.executive.proxy.impl.ExecutiveProxyFactoryImpl" />

 <bean id="docServiceProxyFactory"
   class="gleam.docservice.proxy.impl.DocServiceProxyFactoryImpl" />

6. You are now ready to use default GATE application deployed. For enabling debug in console just edit log4j.properties in WEB-INF/classes by adding this line: log4j.logger.gleam.gateservice=DEBUG
7. If you want to use some different app you must check and probably modify:
a) plugins folder (copy necessary plugins here)
b) resources folder (copy necessary resources, grammars, ontologies, etc)
c) server-definition.xml (specify the input parameters, this GaS application demands)
d) application.xgapp (GATE application itself with fixed paths to plugins and resources (use relpath instead of absolute paths)

